‚ú®The Fortuna River waterfall is located in a biological reserve with an area of 210 acres of transition premontane tropical wet forest, part of the Arenal Volcano National Park and is located at 520 meters over the sea level, where there are sources of our mountains and the waters of the Fortuna River. Within this sector is the Cerro de los Perdidos, Placas de Mayo and Cerro Chato, which are based on rocky foundations of great geological value, causing in turn a lush and scenic beauty. üòç

‚ú®To observe this splendid 70 meters high waterfall, visitors must pass a path of approximately 530 steps, which offers greater security to its passage and comfortable areas for rest and hydration through a forest with native trees of the area. Once in front of the waterfall, you will find a spacious and comfortable vantage point from which you can freeze your memories using unique and previously unpublished photographs, and finally take a refreshing swim in the clear waters of the Fortuna River, with an only witness (the River Fortune waterfall). ‚ô•Ô∏è‚ô•Ô∏è";}i:121;a:1:{s:14:"comments_count";i:1;}i:122;a:1:{s:11:"likes_count";i:1;}i:123;a:1:{s:4:"link";s:39:"https://www.instagram.com/p/CEucd_IpbKd";}i:124;a:1:{s:5:"image";s:259:"https://scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.2885-15/e35/s1080x1080/118775916_168899351392617_2362166772327393922_n.jpg?_nc_ht=scontent-sin6-2.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=109&_nc_ohc=uoEes24SsAIAX-T82iK&_nc_tp=15&oh=0f8a40a0df119beaad3f2ba0df4f0b56&oe=5F7DB753";}i:125;a:1:{s:4:"type";s:5:"image";}i:126;a:1:{s:8:"owner_id";i:40488616746;}i:127;a:1:{s:14:"owner_username";s:0:"";}i:128;a:1:{s:14:"owner_fullname";s:0:"";}i:129;a:1:{s:9:"owner_pic";s:0:"";}i:130;a:1:{s:2:"id";s:19:"2390972679757679539";}i:131;a:1:{s:10:"short_code";s:11:"CEucPv8nsuz";}i:132;a:1:{s:12:"created_time";i:1599246176;}i:133;a:1:{s:7:"caption";s:997:"Starting this Friday I want to share a series honoring my culture and heritage. Introducing ‚ÄúFilipino Friday‚Äôs‚Äù with my with My Lola‚Äôs Sari-Sari store (grandmother‚Äôs small convenient store.)
.
‚ÄúSari-Sari‚Äù basically means a variety. There are so many sari-sari stores in almost every neighborhood throughout the Philippines, even in the most rural areas. These little stores are essential for everyday necessities and sell even things like school supplies. This one is drawn after my grandmothers store. ‚ù§Ô∏è 
.
